00:02:17,909 --> 00:02:28,893
[SPEAKER_01]: So dear Mayor Ilango Kern and members of the school committee, as the year winds down to a close, it is hard to believe that there are only six weeks of school left to this academic year.

34
00:02:30,034 --> 00:02:35,916
[SPEAKER_01]: As I had the opportunity to gather data and reflect on this past year, there was so much to be proud of.

35
00:02:36,517 --> 00:02:43,519
[SPEAKER_01]: And yet at the same time, during the most difficult times, there were many lessons learned from crises.

36
00:02:45,040 --> 00:02:49,983
[SPEAKER_01]: I can say that looking back, I have grown both professionally and personally this school year.

37
00:02:50,843 --> 00:02:58,128
[SPEAKER_01]: As I forge ahead, I am determined to stay focused on what is important and positive, our students and our staff.

38
00:02:59,108 --> 00:03:10,855
[SPEAKER_01]: The Medford Public Schools, currently we are at an important crossroads and through thoughtful community and family collaboration, we will continue to improve and thrive as a district.

39
00:03:12,316 --> 00:03:19,141
[SPEAKER_01]: I will provide a few brief highlights now, but I look forward to taking you on my journey with the Medford Public Schools this year.

40
00:03:20,963 --> 00:03:31,571
[SPEAKER_01]: The Medford Public Schools continues to be an inclusive school district, rich in history and diversity, which offers so many educational opportunities for our students.

41
00:03:32,792 --> 00:03:39,797
[SPEAKER_01]: We encourage our parents and caregivers to collaborate and to partner in their students' educational processes.

42
00:03:41,531 --> 00:03:47,519
[SPEAKER_01]: My aces of achievement collaboration equity and support guide me in my duties daily.

43
00:03:48,521 --> 00:03:57,734
[SPEAKER_01]: Additionally, social emotional learning continues to be a cornerstone of our district, along with responsive classroom and restorative practices.

44
00:03:59,004 --> 00:04:07,892
[SPEAKER_01]: This year we work to hire additional guidance counselors and social workers adjustment counselors school psychologists, teachers and many more.

45
00:04:08,613 --> 00:04:23,086
[SPEAKER_01]: We join the Sandy Hook promise to teach our students to start with hello, see something say something initiative, and new to us this year, we implemented the new say something anonymous reporting system.

46
00:04:24,387 --> 00:04:31,769
[SPEAKER_01]: in an effort to empower everyone, students and staff, to help create change and promote safer schools.

47
00:04:33,069 --> 00:04:51,033
[SPEAKER_01]: We also implemented a 10-point action plan at Medford High School for safety, transparency, culture, climate, and accountability, which did include the Sandy Hook promise, updating the handbook, and implementing new hall and bathroom passes for students.

48
00:04:52,730 --> 00:05:03,469
[SPEAKER_01]: Additionally, we offered viewings of screenagers presentations for our middle school students and parents and caregivers to help them be aware of the dangers of too much screen time.

49
00:05:04,933 --> 00:05:09,414
[SPEAKER_01]: In my practice, I continue to bring an equity lens to all the work that I do.

